ischer Bezüge liefert Luise Reitstätter Antworten und veranschaulicht ortsspezifische Eigenlogiken des Sozialraums Ausstellung.  aExhibitions are socially competitive spaces. They see negotiations about who shall speak and who shall be heard. In the spatial mediation, (sub-)conscious intentions of exhibitors meet the presumed interpretations of visitors. But what really happens in this setting? So far, research primarily regarded art historical staging analyses and empirical visitor research in separation. Questions about the relationship between humans and objects in the room were asked quite rarely. Through extensive field research and spatial and agent theories, Luise Reitstätter gives answers and visualizes the local logic of exhibitions as social spaces.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aArtvExhibitions. 4aBesucherforschung. 4aGrounded Theory. 4aKunst. 4aMuseum. 4aMuseumspädagogik. 4aMuseumswissenschaft. 4aQualitative Sozialforschung. 4aRaum. 4aRaumsoziologie. 7aART / Museum Studies.2bisacsh  aArt.  aGrounded Theory.  aMuseology.  aMuseum Education.  aMuseum.  aQualitative Social Research.  aSociology of Space.  aSpace.  aVisitor Research.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070099208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839429884zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn